        <headline>Special Weather Statement issued May 2 at 8:30AM CDT by NWS Little Rock AR</headline>
        <description>At 830 AM CDT, Doppler radar was tracking a strong thunderstorm near
Oppelo, or near Perryville, moving northeast at 45 mph.

HAZARD...Nickel size hail.

SOURCE...Radar indicated.

IMPACT...Minor damage to outdoor objects is possible.

Locations impacted include...
Petit Jean State Park...          Sequoya Park...
Hill Creek...                     Overcup...
Bethlehem...                      Mt Olive in Conway County...
Solgohachia...                    Menifee...
Morrilton...                      Birdtown...
Kenwood...                        Oppelo...
Springfield...                    Middleton...
Plumerville...                    Ada...
Perry...                          Adona...
</description>
        <instruction>If outdoors, consider seeking shelter inside a building.</instruction>
